    "impact_and_application": [
      "Stoicism, as presented in Meditations, has profoundly influenced Western thought, shaping ethics, psychology, and even political theory.",
      "The emphasis on self-control, reason, and duty has resonated with leaders, thinkers, and individuals seeking guidance in navigating life's challenges. Stoic principles form the basis of cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT), a widely used approach to treating mental health issues. For example, the practice of identifying and challenging negative thoughts is rooted in the Stoic idea that our judgments, not external events, cause our suffering."
